  "body": "I have a simple component with the following state:\n\n```\n{number:1}\n```\n\n... with a simple 'componentDidUpdate' function like this:\n\n```\ncomponentDidUpdate: function(prevProps, prevState){\n  console.log(prevState.number, this.state.number);\n}\n```\n\nThen if I change the state by using the method 'setState'...\n\n```\nthis.setState({number:2});\n```\n\n... 'componentDidUpdate' is fired and I get the following values:\n\n```\nprevState.number --> 1\nthis.state.number --> 2\n```\n\nWhich are good as expected, of course.\nBut if I do something like this:\n\n```\nthis.state.number = 3;\nthis.forceUpdate();\n```\n\n... 'componentDidUpdate' is fired alright, but I get the following unexpected values:\n\n```\nprevState.number --> 3\nthis.state.number --> 3\n```\n\nIs there any workaround so that we still get proper value in 'prevState' ?\n",
